" type="image/png" length="50005" /> </item> <item> <title>Thoughts</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;Following are my personal thoughts on tech, AI, startups and adoption of AI in Health-Care. You could read more about me &lt;a href=&#34;./about.md&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;hr style=&#34;borde...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/thoughts/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/thoughts/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/thoughts.png" type="image/png" length="48720" /> </item> <item> <title>Benchmarking LLM performance on structured data extraction</title> <author>hjaveed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Benchmarking LLM performance on structured data extraction&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;Lot of true enterprise value lies in un-strucuted data&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/future/benchmarking-strucutred-data-extraction/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/future/benchmarking-strucutred-data-extraction/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/future/benchmarking-strucutred-data-extraction.png" type="image/png" length="71406" /> </item> <item> <title>From surfacing actions to taking actions</title> <description></description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/future/from-surfacing-actions-to-taking-actions/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/future/from-surfacing-actions-to-taking-actions/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/future/from-surfacing-actions-to-taking-actions.png" type="image/png" length="69609" /> </item> <item> <title>Journey of learning integrations with Epic and FHIR</title> <author>hjaveed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Journey of learning integrations with Epic and FHIR&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;In past I&#39;ve used middlewares like Redox and Xealth to connect custom developed health-care applicatio...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/future/learning-epic-and-fhir/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/future/learning-epic-and-fhir/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/future/learning-epic-and-fhir.png" type="image/png" length="71337" /> </item> <item> <title>From Concept to Production with Observability in LLM Applications</title> <author>Hadi Javeed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;From Concept to Production with Observability in LLM Applications&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;Understanding observability in AI applications, particularly in Large Language Models (LLMs), is crucial. It&#39;s all about tracking how your model performs over time, which is especially challenging with text generation outputs. Unlike categorical outputs, text generation can vary widely, making it essential to monitor the behavior and performance of your model closely.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/2024/03/05/tracing-and-observability-in-llm-applications/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/2024/03/05/tracing-and-observability-in-llm-applications/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/posts/Tracing-and-Observability-in-LLM-Applications.png" type="image/png" length="72661" /> </item> <item> <title>Is Your Security Posture Holding Your Healthcare Startup Back?</title> <author>Hadi Javeed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Is Your Security Posture Holding Your Healthcare Startup Back?&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;When deploying a healthcare product, HIPAA compliance is crucial. No matter how innovative your solution is, without convincing the CIO or security team, you won&#39;t get deployed. I view security and HIPAA posture as essential features of any healthcare product.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/2024/10/23/is-your-security-posture-holding-your-healthcare-startup-back/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/2024/10/23/is-your-security-posture-holding-your-healthcare-startup-back/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/posts/advice-on-hipaa-and-cloud.png" type="image/png" length="73854" /> </item> <item> <title>AI Gave Engineers 20 Hours Back Per Week. Why Aren&#39;t We Shipping Faster?</title> <author>Hadi Javeed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;AI Gave Engineers 20 Hours Back Per Week. Why Aren&#39;t We Shipping Faster?&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;AI has compressed time in my life. This time compression has unlocked a lot, but perhaps not in the ways you&#39;d expect.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Nothing you don&#39;t already know, right?&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/2025/07/26/ai-productivity-paradox-faster-not-smarter/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/2025/07/26/ai-productivity-paradox-faster-not-smarter/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/posts/ai-productivity-paradox-faster-not-smarter.png" type="image/png" length="77996" /> </item> <item> <title>Does Your Startup Really Need Complex Cloud Infrastructure?</title> <author>Hadi Javeed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Does Your Startup Really Need Complex Cloud Infrastructure?&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;I recently listened to &lt;a href=&#34;https://x.com/levelsio&#34;&gt;Pieter Levels&lt;/a&gt;{:target=&#34;_blank&#34;} on the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oFtjKbXKqbg&amp;amp;ab_channel=LexFridman&#34;&gt;Lex Friedman Podcast&lt;/a&gt;{:target=&#34;_blank&#34;}, and it was eye-opening. Pieter has built numerous successful micro-SaaS businesses by running his applications on single server, avoiding cloud infrastructure complexity, and focusing on what truly matters: product-market fit.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/2024/09/08/does-your-startup-really-need-complex-cloud-infrastructure/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/2024/09/08/does-your-startup-really-need-complex-cloud-infrastructure/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/posts/avoiding-cloud-infra-complexity.png" type="image/png" length="72753" /> </item> <item> <title>Blueprint and Engineering Principles</title> <author>Hadi Javeed</author> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Blueprint and Engineering Principles&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;These are the principles we follow at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.revelaihealth.com/&#34;&gt;RevelAI Health&lt;/a&gt;{:target=&#34;_blank&#34;}. They&#39;ve shaped how we build and ship. Might be useful for other early to late stage startups too.&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://hadijaveed.me/2025/12/24/product-and-engineering-principles/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 Dec 2025 23:16:04 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://hadijaveed.me/feed_rss_updated.xml">Hadi Javeed's blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://hadijaveed.me/2025/12/24/product-and-engineering-principles/</guid> <enclosure url="https://hadijaveed.me/assets/images/social/posts/blue-print-and-engineering=principles.png" type="image/png" length="63563" /> </item> </channel> </rss>